## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js App Router project.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics component integration
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated lock file with new dependency

### Implementation Details

1. **Fetched Latest Documentation**: Retrieved the most up-to-date installation instructions from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart

2. **Framework Detection**: Identified this as a Next.js project using App Router based on:
   - Next.js 16.2.6 in package.json
   - App directory structure with app/layout.tsx

3. **Package Installation**: 
   - Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm (the project's package manager)
   - Package version installed: Latest version from npm registry
   - Lock file properly updated

4. **Analytics Integration**:
   - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
   - Placed `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag in the root layout
   - Follows Next.js App Router best practices as specified in official documentation

### Code Changes

**app/layout.tsx**:
- Added Analytics import from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Inserted `<Analytics />` component inside the body element, after children
- Preserved all existing code structure and styling

### Verification

✅ **Linting**: The modified layout.tsx file passes ESLint without errors
✅ **Lock Files**: package-lock.json properly updated with new dependencies
✅ **Code Quality**: Changes follow Next.js conventions and TypeScript best practices

### Notes

- The build test encountered a pre-existing Supabase configuration error (`supabaseUrl is required`) unrelated to the Analytics installation
- Pre-existing linting errors in `app/overlay/Overlay.tsx` are unrelated to this change
- Analytics will automatically start collecting data once deployed to Vercel
- No additional configuration is required - the component works out of the box

### Next Steps (Post-Deployment)

After deploying to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard if not already enabled
2. Verify Analytics is working by checking the Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`
3. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics section
